---
import Base from '../../../layouts/Base.astro';
const title = 'Three Paths';
const subtitle = 'Pick your path. The wrong one is the cascade.';
---
<Base title={title} description={subtitle}>
  <article class="etude-page">
    <header class="etude-head">
      <p class="etude-kicker">Etude · Campaign Cascade</p>
      <h1 class="etude-title">{title}</h1>
      <p class="etude-relief">{subtitle}</p>
      <nav class="etude-nav">
        <a href="/etudes/campaign-cascade/">← campaign cascade etudes</a>
        <span class="etude-nav-sep">·</span>
        <a href="/puzzles/the-campaign-cascade/">essay</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <section class="etude-intro">
      <p>Every cross-cutting initiative has three valid responses: <strong>centralize</strong> the work, <strong>automate</strong> it end-to-end, or <strong>cut scope</strong> to where the change actually delivers value. Most failures pick the wrong one — and the wrong pick is what spawns the next campaign.</p>
      <p>Four scenarios. Pick a path for each. Instant feedback.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="etude-progress" id="dots" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div id="stage" class="etude-stage" aria-live="polite"></div>

    <footer class="etude-coda">
      <p>Most cascades start with a centralize answer where automate would have worked, or an automate answer where the right call was to cut scope. The path itself is half the work.</p>
    </footer>
  </article>
</Base>

<script is:inline>
  const SCENARIOS = [
    {
      title: 'Migrate 800 services to Java 21',
      context: 'Hypothetical fleet. Perf wins are the motivation — measurable latency and GC improvements. Owners scattered across dozens of teams. Target: end of next quarter.',
      best: 'B',
      feedback: {
        A: { verdict: 'wrong', text: 'Centralizing creates a platform-team bottleneck. 800 services through one queue means the migration drags past the quarter, perf wins arrive late, and the platform team becomes the next campaign.' },
        B: { verdict: 'right', text: 'A codemod fits. The change is mechanical, the perf payoff requires hitting all 800, and one PR per service keeps team ownership intact. Tradeoff: you invest in the codemod up front. Worth it.' },
        C: { verdict: 'wrong', text: 'Cutting scope undercuts the perf work that motivated this. If you only migrate the hot services, you keep two runtimes forever and pay the operational tax twice.' }
      }
    },
    {
      title: 'Roll out a new auth library across 200 services',
      context: 'Hypothetical fleet. No perf change. Security review wants consistent integration across every surface. Test surface is mixed — some services have great coverage, some have none.',
      best: 'A',
      feedback: {
        A: { verdict: 'right', text: 'Centralize. Security review needs one integration pattern, not 200. A platform team owning the rollout end-to-end keeps the threat model consistent. Tradeoff: slower than a codemod, but the consistency is the point.' },
        B: { verdict: 'partial', text: 'A codemod can work where test coverage is good — but on services with no coverage, you ship a security change blind. Most teams pick this and pay later. Centralize is the safer call.' },
        C: { verdict: 'wrong', text: 'You cannot cut scope on auth. Either every service is on the new library or your threat model has a hole. This is the scenario where scope-cutting is genuinely wrong.' }
      }
    },
    {
      title: 'Get every team to add structured logging',
      context: 'Hypothetical fleet. The actual pain: on-call pages from ~30 services where unstructured logs make root-causing slow. The other 170 services rarely page anyone.',
      best: 'C',
      feedback: {
        A: { verdict: 'wrong', text: 'Centralizing this means a platform team chasing 200 service owners for a change most of them get no value from. Compliance theater. The logging campaign becomes a year-long open thread.' },
        B: { verdict: 'wrong', text: 'A codemod ships structured logging everywhere — but the value only lands in the 30 services that page. You spent the codemod budget on services that will never benefit. Right tool, wrong target.' },
        C: { verdict: 'right', text: 'Cut scope. Structured logging in the 30 services that drive on-call pain delivers the entire value of the campaign. The other 170 can wait until they actually page.' }
      }
    },
    {
      title: 'Decommission the legacy event bus by Q3',
      context: 'Hypothetical fleet. ~150 services publish or subscribe to it. New bus exists. Hard deadline — old bus contract ends Q3. Need both code changes and a coordinated cutover calendar.',
      best: 'AB',
      feedback: {
        A: { verdict: 'partial', text: 'Centralize alone gets you the rollout calendar but leaves teams hand-editing 150 codebases. Doable, but slow — and a hard deadline punishes slow.' },
        B: { verdict: 'partial', text: 'A codemod handles the code change cleanly. But cutover order matters (publishers before subscribers, or vice versa) and that is a calendar problem the codemod cannot solve. Half the answer.' },
        AB: { verdict: 'right', text: 'Codemod plus central ownership of the rollout calendar. The codemod handles 150 mechanical changes; the central team sequences the cutover so nothing breaks mid-flight. Two paths, composed.' },
        C: { verdict: 'wrong', text: 'Cannot cut scope on a decommission. The old bus contract ends Q3; partial migration means partial outage.' }
      }
    }
  ];

  const stage = document.getElementById('stage');
  const dotsEl = document.getElementById('dots');

  let idx = 0;
  let picks = [];

  function renderDots() {
    const total = SCENARIOS.length;
    dotsEl.innerHTML = SCENARIOS.map((_, i) => {
      const cls = i < idx ? 'etude-dot etude-dot-done' : i === idx ? 'etude-dot etude-dot-current' : 'etude-dot';
      return `<span class="${cls}" aria-label="step ${i+1} of ${total}"></span>`;
    }).join('');
  }

  function renderScenario() {
    renderDots();
    const s = SCENARIOS[idx];
    const isCombo = s.best === 'AB';
    stage.innerHTML = `
      <div class="etude-card">
        <p class="etude-step">Scenario ${idx + 1} of ${SCENARIOS.length}</p>
        <h2 class="etude-card-title">${s.title}</h2>
        <p class="etude-card-context">${s.context}</p>
        <div class="etude-choices" role="group" aria-label="Pick a path">
          <button type="button" class="etude-choice" data-pick="A">
            <span class="etude-choice-label"><span class="etude-choice-letter">A</span>Centralize</span>
            <span class="etude-choice-desc">A platform team owns the work end-to-end. Service teams get a PR and a Slack DM.</span>
          </button>
          <button type="button" class="etude-choice" data-pick="B">
            <span class="etude-choice-label"><span class="etude-choice-letter">B</span>Automate</span>
            <span class="etude-choice-desc">Codemod the change everywhere. Service teams get a single PR they review.</span>
          </button>
          <button type="button" class="etude-choice" data-pick="C">
            <span class="etude-choice-label"><span class="etude-choice-letter">C</span>Cut scope</span>
            <span class="etude-choice-desc">Apply only where the change actually delivers value. Leave the rest.</span>
          </button>
          ${isCombo ? `
          <button type="button" class="etude-choice etude-choice-combo" data-pick="AB">
            <span class="etude-choice-label"><span class="etude-choice-letter">A+B</span>Combine</span>
            <span class="etude-choice-desc">Codemod the code change. Central team owns the rollout calendar.</span>
          </button>` : ''}
        </div>
        <div class="etude-feedback" id="feedback"></div>
      </div>
    `;
    stage.querySelectorAll('.etude-choice').forEach(btn => {
      btn.addEventListener('click', () => handlePick(btn.dataset.pick));
    });
  }

  function handlePick(pick) {
    const s = SCENARIOS[idx];
    const fb = s.feedback[pick] || { verdict: 'wrong', text: 'Not a path that fits this scenario.' };
    const correct = pick === s.best;
    picks.push({ pick, correct, best: s.best });

    stage.querySelectorAll('.etude-choice').forEach(btn => {
      btn.disabled = true;
      if (btn.dataset.pick === pick) btn.classList.add('etude-choice-picked');
      if (btn.dataset.pick === s.best) btn.classList.add('etude-choice-correct');
    });

    const fbEl = document.getElementById('feedback');
    const verdictLabel = fb.verdict === 'right' ? 'Right path' : fb.verdict === 'partial' ? 'Partial fit' : 'Wrong path';
    fbEl.innerHTML = `
      <div class="etude-verdict etude-verdict-${fb.verdict}">
        <p class="etude-verdict-label">${verdictLabel}</p>
        <p class="etude-verdict-text">${fb.text}</p>
        <button type="button" class="etude-next" id="next-btn">${idx + 1 < SCENARIOS.length ? 'Next scenario' : 'See your score'}</button>
      </div>
    `;
    document.getElementById('next-btn').addEventListener('click', advance);
  }

  function advance() {
    idx += 1;
    if (idx < SCENARIOS.length) {
      renderScenario();
    } else {
      renderScore();
    }
  }

  function renderScore() {
    renderDots();
    const counts = { A: 0, B: 0, C: 0, AB: 0 };
    let wrong = 0;
    picks.forEach(p => {
      counts[p.pick] = (counts[p.pick] || 0) + 1;
      if (!p.correct) wrong += 1;
    });
    const right = picks.length - wrong;
    const summary = wrong === 0
      ? 'Clean run. You read each scenario for what it actually rewards.'
      : wrong === picks.length
        ? 'Every pick was the cascade-spawning one. Worth re-reading the scenarios — the wrong path always looked plausible.'
        : 'Most failures look like this — one or two wrong calls, each one defensible in isolation. The cascade is built from defensible wrong calls.';
    stage.innerHTML = `
      <div class="etude-card etude-card-score">
        <p class="etude-step">Done</p>
        <p class="etude-score-headline"><span class="etude-score-fraction">${right}<span class="etude-score-divider">/</span>${picks.length}</span> right</p>
        <p class="etude-score-mix">You picked centralize ${counts.A}, automate ${counts.B}, cut scope ${counts.C}${counts.AB ? `, combine ${counts.AB}` : ''}.</p>
        <p class="etude-score-detail">${summary}</p>
        <button type="button" class="etude-next" id="restart-btn">Run it again</button>
      </div>
    `;
    document.getElementById('restart-btn').addEventListener('click', restart);
  }

  function restart() {
    idx = 0;
    picks = [];
    renderScenario();
  }

  renderScenario();
</script>

<style is:global>
  /* === etude page chrome === */
  .etude-page {
    max-width: 38rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .etude-head {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .etude-kicker {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: var(--label-size);
    letter-spacing: var(--label-tracking);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
  }
  .etude-title {
    font-family: var(--serif-display);
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .etude-relief {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    line-height: 1.45;
  }
  .etude-nav {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--muted);
  }
  .etude-nav a { color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none; }
  .etude-nav a:hover { color: var(--accent); }
  .etude-nav-sep { margin: 0 0.5rem; opacity: 0.5; }

  .etude-intro {
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }
  .etude-intro p {
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* === progress === */
  .etude-progress {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin: 2rem 0 1.25rem;
    justify-content: center;
  }
  .etude-dot {
    width: 0.5rem;
    height: 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--line);
    transition: background 240ms ease, transform 240ms ease, box-shadow 240ms ease;
  }
  .etude-dot-done {
    background: var(--accent);
  }
  .etude-dot-current {
    background: var(--accent);
    transform: scale(1.4);
  }

  .etude-stage {
    min-height: 22rem;
  }

  /* === scenario card === */
  .etude-card {
    background: var(--bg-soft);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.5rem 1.5rem 1.25rem;
  }
  .etude-step {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: var(--label-size);
    letter-spacing: var(--label-tracking);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
  }
  .etude-card-title {
    font-family: var(--serif-display);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.25;
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .etude-card-context {
    margin: 0 0 1.4rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  /* === choices === */
  .etude-choices {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.6rem;
  }
  .etude-choice {
    appearance: none;
    -webkit-appearance: none;
    font-family: inherit;
    text-align: left;
    background: var(--bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
    min-height: 2.75rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.3rem;
    color: var(--text);
    transition: border-color 180ms ease, background 180ms ease, transform 120ms ease, box-shadow 180ms ease;
  }
  .etude-choice:hover:not(:disabled) {
    border-color: var(--accent);
    background: var(--bg);
    box-shadow: 0 1px 3px rgba(43, 37, 32, 0.06);
  }
  .etude-choice:active:not(:disabled) {
    transform: scale(0.99);
  }
  .etude-choice:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid var(--accent);
    outline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .etude-choice:disabled {
    cursor: default;
    opacity: 0.55;
  }
  .etude-choice-label {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.55rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .etude-choice-letter {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 1.5rem;
    height: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--line);
    color: var(--text);
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    transition: background 180ms ease, color 180ms ease;
  }
  .etude-choice:hover:not(:disabled) .etude-choice-letter {
    background: var(--accent);
    color: var(--bg);
  }
  .etude-choice-desc {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
    padding-left: 2.05rem;
  }
  .etude-choice-combo {
    border-style: dashed;
  }
  .etude-choice-picked {
    opacity: 1;
    border-color: var(--accent);
    background: rgba(138, 52, 32, 0.06);
  }
  .etude-choice-picked .etude-choice-letter {
    background: var(--accent);
    color: var(--bg);
  }
  .etude-choice-correct {
    opacity: 1;
    border-color: #2d7a3e;
    background: rgba(45, 122, 62, 0.05);
  }
  .etude-choice-correct .etude-choice-letter {
    background: #2d7a3e;
    color: white;
  }
  .etude-choice-picked.etude-choice-correct {
    background: rgba(45, 122, 62, 0.1);
  }

  /* === verdict === */
  .etude-feedback:not(:empty) {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }
  .etude-verdict {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    padding-top: 1.1rem;
  }
  .etude-verdict-label {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 0.55rem;
  }
  .etude-verdict-right .etude-verdict-label { color: #2d7a3e; }
  .etude-verdict-partial .etude-verdict-label { color: #b87333; }
  .etude-verdict-wrong .etude-verdict-label { color: var(--accent); }
  .etude-verdict-text {
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  /* === next button === */
  .etude-next {
    appearance: none;
    -webkit-appearance: none;
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    padding: 0.65rem 1.2rem;
    border: none;
    background: var(--text);
    color: var(--bg);
    border-radius: 999px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background 180ms ease, transform 120ms ease;
  }
  .etude-next:hover {
    background: var(--accent);
  }
  .etude-next:active {
    transform: scale(0.97);
  }
  .etude-next:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid var(--accent);
    outline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .etude-next::after {
    content: ' →';
  }

  /* === score === */
  .etude-card-score {
    text-align: left;
  }
  .etude-score-headline {
    font-family: var(--serif-display);
    font-size: 2rem;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .etude-score-fraction {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .etude-score-divider {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-weight: 400;
    margin: 0 0.05em;
  }
  .etude-score-mix {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
  .etude-score-detail {
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  /* === coda === */
  .etude-coda {
    margin: 2.5rem 0 0;
    padding-top: 1.25rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .etude-coda p {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* === mobile === */
  @media (max-width: 32rem) {
    .etude-title { font-size: 1.85rem; }
    .etude-card { padding: 1.15rem 1.1rem 1rem; border-radius: 10px; }
    .etude-card-title { font-size: 1.3rem; }
    .etude-choice { padding: 0.75rem 0.85rem; }
    .etude-choice-desc { padding-left: 0; }
  }
</style>
